 <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Crophull was born about 1410. She married Sir John De Parr about 1414. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1470, at the age of 61."},"et":{"about 1410–1470":"umbes 1410–1470","1410–1465":"1410–1465","1394–1438":"1394–1438","1410–1470":"1410–1470","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","about 1414":"umbes 1414","1394":"1394","about 1410":"umbes 1410","1470":"1470","1438":"1438","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"about 1410–1470":"noin 1410–1470","1410–1465":"1410–1465","1394–1438":"1394–1438","1410–1470":"1410–1470","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","about 1414":"noin 1414","1394":"1394","about 1410":"noin 1410","1470":"1470","1438":"1438","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"about 1410–1470":"environ 1410–1470","1410–1465":"1410–1465","1394–1438":"1394–1438","1410–1470":"1410–1470","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","about 1414":"environ 1414","1394":"1394","about 1410":"environ 1410","1470":"1470","1438":"1438","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Agnes Crophull est née environ 1410. Elle a épousé Sir John De Parr environ 1414. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1470, à l’âge de 61 ans."},"de":{"about 1410–1470":"um 1410–1470","1410–1465":"1410–1465","1394–1438":"1394–1438","1410–1470":"1410–1470","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","about 1414":"um 1414","1394":"1394","about 1410":"um 1410","1470":"1470","1438":"1438","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","lifeSummary":"Agnes Crophull wurde um 1410 geboren. Sie hat um 1414 Sir John De Parr geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 